servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened,
~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.
> Be sure to measure the garlic powder; you'll use the rest in the next step.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and bell pepper; cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until sausage is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, half the @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} (you'll use the rest later),
@water{1/2%cup}, and remaining @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until sauce is
bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Spread cut
sides with garlic butter. Place cut sides up on a #baking sheet{}. Toast on middle rack
until bread is golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.
> TIP: Line sheet with foil first for easier cleanup.

Carefully spoon sausage and pepper mixture onto bottom halves; top with
@mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Return to middle rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%oz} with remaining vinegar and a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide salad and sandwiches between plates and serve.